        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 5:58PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Scattered convective snow showers will impact areas south of the
US Highway 87/Montana Highway 200 Corridor this evening. This
includes the I-15 and I-90 corridor.

Some snow showers will become locally intense, quickly reducing
visibilities to a mile or less at times. Warm pavements will keep
accumulations to less than a half of an inch at lower elevations
with 1 to 3 inches in the mountains. However, snow rates of a
half an inch per hour with more intense showers can accumulate
light, slushy accumulations on roadways quickly. Bridges and
elevated surfaces can become slippery and slushy from wet
pavements.
</description>
